A campaign to make shoppers more aware of the upcoming introduction of charges for carrier bags has been launched by Scotland's Environment Secretary. New carrier bag charge awareness drive is launched A campaign to make shoppers more aware of the upcoming introduction of charges for carrier bags has been launched by Scotland's Environment Secretary.Richard Lochhead began the public awareness drive at the Gyle shopping centre, in Edinburgh, ahead of the introduction of the charge on &shy;October 20.From that date it will cost at least 5p for each single-use carrier bag given out to shoppers regardless of where they shop, from supermarkets to corner shops and takeaways to high street retailers. 